  keywords="is mm a scrabble word, mm scrabble, mm sowpods only, mm valid scrabble, vowelless scrabble words, mm meaning scrabble, double m scrabble word"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Is MM a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only — NOT Valid in TWL (6 Points)", "description": "MM is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL. It scores 6 points (M=3, M=3) and is an interjection expressing pleasure or agreement.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-mm-a-scrabble-word" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is MM a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MM is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (International/Collins dictionary). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List used in North America). MM scores 6 points (M=3, M=3) and is an interjection expressing pleasure, agreement, or satisfaction — like saying 'mmm, that's good'. It's also notable as a vowelless word." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is MM worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MM scores 6 points in Scrabble (M=3 + M=3). It's one of the highest-scoring 2-letter words because both tiles are worth 3 points each. On a Double Letter square, MM scores 9 points. On a Double Word square, it scores 12 points. Compare this to most 2-letter words which score 2-4 points." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is MM a vowelless Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — MM contains zero vowels. It's entirely consonants (two M tiles). In SOWPODS games, MM is one of the rare vowelless 2-letter words, alongside SH (5pts) and HM (7pts). This makes it invaluable when your rack is loaded with consonants and you can't find a vowel to use." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is MM a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">MM is valid in SOWPODS (International) but NOT in TWL (North American). At 6 points from just 2 tiles, MM is one of the highest-scoring two-letter words in the game — because each M is worth 3 points. It's an interjection expressing pleasure or agreement ("mmm, that's delicious"), and crucially, it contains no vowels. A perfect emergency play when consonants dominate your rack.</p>

