        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Most 2-letter words use 1-point tiles (E, A, I, O, S, T, R, N). MM is exceptional because <span class="text-white font-medium">both tiles score 3 points</span>. That's 6 points from 2 tiles — matching the scoring rate of many 4-5 letter words. On premium squares, MM becomes even more powerful: M on Double Letter = 9pts total, MM on Double Word = 12pts.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Vowelless Words Comparison</h2>
      <p>MM joins a small club of vowelless Scrabble words. Here's how the 2-letter vowelless words compare:</p>
