          <span class="text-white font-bold">SHH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts · Both</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: When to Play MM</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Consonant overload rescue:</span> Drew both M tiles with no vowels? MM dumps them both for 6 points without needing a single vowel. This frees rack space to draw vowels for your next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">M on premium squares:</span> Each M is worth 3 points. On a Double Letter, one M contributes 6 points — making MM score 9 total. On Double Word, MM scores 12 points for just 2 tiles placed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
